reviewText: I could not finish the course.  The split screen learning was difficult to see and navigate.  The instructor was difficult to understand and follow.  She seemed like she either did not know what she was talking about, or had not practiced leading the course before recording it.  She speaks English, but it is heavily accented.  She constantly pauses to say umm and similar words.  She starts talking about one feature, then skips to another feature she just thought of before coming back to finish explaining the original feature.  This course is an utter disaster.

I thought I was going to learn how to build a website, instead, its an "install a plugin", upload 3 files, which we have ready, and the website is ready.  Where do I get the three files for the website I want to build?

What you learn in the course is very basic. The instructor uses a lot of previously prepared content, so most of the time you spend typing. Since this should be beginner friendly, I would like to find out what are plug-ins, what are widgets, where can we learn more about them. What options are theme dependant? Overall, it is a very shallow look at WordPress, that could have taken 15 minutes not 2 hours or so.
